      "span_text": "encoding all the information in the visual image? Some progress has been made in answering this question, but so far the analyses have been rather qualitative and nonrigorous., One goal of this paper is to show how two-dimensional sampling theory can be used to determine which combinations of receptive-field shapes and sampling patterns would preserve all spatial information in the retinal image and which ones would not."
